30static const int CODE_START_A = 103;
31static const int CODE_START_B = 104;
32static const int CODE_START_C = 105;
33static const int CODE_CODE_A = 101;
34static const int CODE_CODE_B = 100;
35static const int CODE_CODE_C = 99;
36static const int CODE_STOP = 106;
37
38// Dummy characters used to specify control characters in input
39static const auto ESCAPE_FNC_1 = L'\u00f1';
40static const auto ESCAPE_FNC_2 = L'\u00f2';
41static const auto ESCAPE_FNC_3 = L'\u00f3';
42static const auto ESCAPE_FNC_4 = L'\u00f4';
43
44static const int CODE_FNC_1 = 102; // Code A, Code B, Code C
45static const int CODE_FNC_2 = 97; // Code A, Code B
46static const int CODE_FNC_3 = 96; // Code A, Code B
47static const int CODE_FNC_4_A = 101; // Code A
48static const int CODE_FNC_4_B = 100; // Code B
49
50 // Results of minimal lookahead for code C
51enum class CType {
52 UNCODABLE,
53 ONE_DIGIT,
54 TWO_DIGITS,
55 FNC_1
56};
57
58static CType FindCType(const std::wstring& value, int start)
59{
60 int last = Size(value);
61 if (start >= last) {
62 return CType::UNCODABLE;
63 }
64 wchar_t c = value[start];
65 if (c == ESCAPE_FNC_1) {
66 return CType::FNC_1;
67 }
68 if (c < '0' || c > '9') {
69 return CType::UNCODABLE;
70 }
71 if (start + 1 >= last) {
72 return CType::ONE_DIGIT;
73 }
74 c = value[start + 1];
75 if (c < '0' || c > '9') {
76 return CType::ONE_DIGIT;
77 }
78 return CType::TWO_DIGITS;
79}
80
81static int ChooseCode(const std::wstring& value, int start, int oldCode)
82{
83 CType lookahead = FindCType(value, start);
84 if (lookahead == CType::ONE_DIGIT) {
85 if (oldCode == CODE_CODE_A) {
86 return CODE_CODE_A;
87 }
88 return CODE_CODE_B;
89 }
90 if (lookahead == CType::UNCODABLE) {
91 if (start < Size(value)) {
92 int c = value[start];
93 if (c < ' ' || (oldCode == CODE_CODE_A && (c < '`' || (c >= ESCAPE_FNC_1 && c <= ESCAPE_FNC_4)))) {
94 // can continue in code A, encodes ASCII 0 to 95 or FNC1 to FNC4
95 return CODE_CODE_A;
96 }
97 }
98 return CODE_CODE_B; // no choice
99 }
100 if (oldCode == CODE_CODE_A && lookahead == CType::FNC_1) {
101 return CODE_CODE_A;
102 }
103 if (oldCode == CODE_CODE_C) { // can continue in code C
104 return CODE_CODE_C;
105 }
106 if (oldCode == CODE_CODE_B) {
107 if (lookahead == CType::FNC_1) {
108 return CODE_CODE_B; // can continue in code B
109 }
110 // Seen two consecutive digits, see what follows
111 lookahead = FindCType(value, start + 2);
112 if (lookahead == CType::UNCODABLE || lookahead == CType::ONE_DIGIT) {
113 return CODE_CODE_B; // not worth switching now
114 }
115 if (lookahead == CType::FNC_1) { // two digits, then FNC_1...
116 lookahead = FindCType(value, start + 3);
117 if (lookahead == CType::TWO_DIGITS) { // then two more digits, switch
118 return CODE_CODE_C;
119 }
120 else {
121 return CODE_CODE_B; // otherwise not worth switching
122 }
123 }
124 // At this point, there are at least 4 consecutive digits.
125 // Look ahead to choose whether to switch now or on the next round.
126 int index = start + 4;
127 while ((lookahead = FindCType(value, index)) == CType::TWO_DIGITS) {
128 index += 2;
129 }
130 if (lookahead == CType::ONE_DIGIT) { // odd number of digits, switch later
131 return CODE_CODE_B;
132 }
133 return CODE_CODE_C; // even number of digits, switch now
134 }
135 // Here oldCode == 0, which means we are choosing the initial code
136 if (lookahead == CType::FNC_1) { // ignore FNC_1
137 lookahead = FindCType(value, start + 1);
138 }
139 if (lookahead == CType::TWO_DIGITS) { // at least two digits, start in code C
140 return CODE_CODE_C;
141 }
142 return CODE_CODE_B;
143}
144
145BitMatrix
146Code128Writer::encode(const std::wstring& contents, int width, int height) const
147{
148 // Check length
149 int length = Size(contents);
150 if (length < 1 || length > 80) {
151 throw std::invalid_argument("Contents length should be between 1 and 80 characters");
152 }
153
154 // Check content
155 for (int i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
156 int c = contents[i];
157 switch (c) {
158 case ESCAPE_FNC_1:
159 case ESCAPE_FNC_2:
160 case ESCAPE_FNC_3:
161 case ESCAPE_FNC_4:
162 break;
163 default:
164 if (c > 127) {
165 // support for FNC4 isn't implemented, no full Latin-1 character set available at the moment
166 throw std::invalid_argument(std::string("Bad character in input: ") + static_cast<char>(c));
167 }
168 }
169 }
170
171 std::list<std::vector<int>> patterns; // temporary storage for patterns
172 int checkSum = 0;
173 int checkWeight = 1;
174 int codeSet = 0; // selected code (CODE_CODE_B or CODE_CODE_C)
175 int position = 0; // position in contents
176
177 while (position < length) {
178 //Select code to use
179 int newCodeSet = ChooseCode(contents, position, codeSet);
180
181 //Get the pattern index
182 int patternIndex;
183 if (newCodeSet == codeSet) {
184 // Encode the current character
185 // First handle escapes
186 switch (contents[position]) {
187 case ESCAPE_FNC_1:
188 patternIndex = CODE_FNC_1;
189 break;
190 case ESCAPE_FNC_2:
191 patternIndex = CODE_FNC_2;
192 break;
193 case ESCAPE_FNC_3:
194 patternIndex = CODE_FNC_3;
195 break;
196 case ESCAPE_FNC_4:
197 if (codeSet == CODE_CODE_A) {
198 patternIndex = CODE_FNC_4_A;
199 }
200 else {
201 patternIndex = CODE_FNC_4_B;
202 }
203 break;
204 default:
205 // Then handle normal characters otherwise
206 if (codeSet == CODE_CODE_A) {
207 patternIndex = contents[position] - ' ';
208 if (patternIndex < 0) {
209 // everything below a space character comes behind the underscore in the code patterns table
210 patternIndex += '`';
211 }
212 }
213 else if (codeSet == CODE_CODE_B) {
214 patternIndex = contents[position] - ' ';
215 }
216 else { // CODE_CODE_C
217 patternIndex = (contents[position] - '0') * 10 + (position+1 < length ? contents[position+1] - '0' : 0);
218 position++; // Also incremented below
219 }
220 }
221 position++;
222 }
223 else {
224 // Should we change the current code?
225 // Do we have a code set?
226 if (codeSet == 0) {
227 // No, we don't have a code set
228 if (newCodeSet == CODE_CODE_A) {
229 patternIndex = CODE_START_A;
230 }
231 else if (newCodeSet == CODE_CODE_B) {
232 patternIndex = CODE_START_B;
233 }
234 else {
235 // CODE_CODE_C
236 patternIndex = CODE_START_C;
237 }
238 }
239 else {
240 // Yes, we have a code set
241 patternIndex = newCodeSet;
242 }
243 codeSet = newCodeSet;
244 }
245
246 // Get the pattern
247 patterns.push_back(Code128::CODE_PATTERNS[patternIndex]);
248
249 // Compute checksum
250 checkSum += patternIndex * checkWeight;
251 if (position != 0) {
252 checkWeight++;
253 }
254 }
255
256 // Compute and append checksum
257 checkSum %= 103;
258 patterns.push_back(Code128::CODE_PATTERNS[checkSum]);
259
260 // Append stop code
261 patterns.push_back(Code128::CODE_PATTERNS[CODE_STOP]);
262
263 // Compute code width
264 int codeWidth = 0;
265 for (const std::vector<int>& pattern : patterns) {
266 codeWidth += std::accumulate(pattern.begin(), pattern.end(), 0);
267 }
268
269 // Compute result
270 std::vector<bool> result(codeWidth, false);
271 int pos = 0;
272 for (const std::vector<int>& pattern : patterns) {
273 pos += WriterHelper::AppendPattern(result, pos, pattern, true);
274 }
275
276 return WriterHelper::RenderResult(result, width, height, _sidesMargin >= 0 ? _sidesMargin : 10);
277}
